              "text": "Registry",
              "kind": "type"
            }
          ],
          "params": [],
          "returnType": null,
          "description": "Registry of navigable Scene constructors, keyed by a name used for diagnostics (shown in UnregisteredSceneError messages and duplicate-registration errors) and for key-based navigation. Each value is either a bare Scene subclass constructor, or a { scene, transition? } descriptor pairing one with a target-bound default transition — see SceneRegistration (transition's real type ships with the transition runtime; it is an inert placeholder until then). Required for any Application.start / SceneDirector.change call that targets a constructor — unregistered targets reject in development builds. Validated once at construction: every value must resolve to a Scene subclass constructor (checked without instantiating it), and no constructor may appear under more than one key."
        },
